{
  "texts": [
    "Neuroimaging at that time demonstrated a large posterior fossa cyst that was associated with significant mass effect on her cerebellum and resultant Chiari malformation.",
    "Four months prior, she underwent fenestration of the cyst with neurosurgery.",
    "She did well in the immediate postoperative period and was discharged home on postoperative day 2.",
    "However, eight days later, she re-presented with wound drainage and underwent wound revision surgery.",
    "No cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) leak was identified, but cultures grew Staphylococcus pseudintermedius."
  ]
}